# .nvmrc File Documentation
#
# This file is used by Node Version Manager (NVM) to specify which version of Node.js to use for the project.
# This file is added to the project to ensure consistent Node.js version usage across different environments.
#
# lts/*: This line tells NVM to use the latest Long Term Support (LTS) version of Node.js.
# LTS versions of Node.js are recommended for most use cases because they receive updates for an extended period of time.

# Use the latest Long Term Support (LTS) version of Node.js
lts/*